The paper proposes a generative model for networks with node attributes, specifically for community detection. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves modeling a joint distribution using a Restricted Boltzmann Machine. It also involves statistical inference (cs.SI) as the authors show that inference can be done efficiently in linear time. The paper also deals with social networks (cs.SD) and systems and control (cs.SY) as it applies the model to real-world networks with attributes. Finally, the use of a generative model for community detection can also fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
